---
description: UI rendering and component responsibility rules
globs:
  - "app/**/*"
  - "features/**/*"
  - "shared/components/**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

# rendering.mdc

- Keep components presentation-focused
- Avoid embedding business rules directly inside JSX
- Move data transformation outside render bodies
- Keep render paths predictable and side-effect free
- Avoid large monolithic components
- Split unrelated UI responsibilities into smaller components
- Prefer composition over prop explosion
- Avoid deeply nested conditional rendering
- Keep conditional branches explicit
- Avoid inline anonymous components inside render functions
- Avoid duplicated rendering branches
- Extract repeated markup patterns
- Keep components narrowly scoped
- Avoid components with excessive prop counts
- Avoid implicit UI state synchronization
- Prefer derived UI over duplicated state
- Keep UI-only state local to components
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders caused by unstable references
- Avoid hidden side effects during rendering
- Keep loading, error, and empty states explicit
- Avoid mixing layout concerns with business orchestration
- Prefer declarative rendering flows
- Keep component trees understandable without runtime context